WorldStage NewsOnline—The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared Gov. Samuel Ortom of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) as winner of the Benue Governorship election in the state. Ortom polled 434,473 votes to defeat his closest rival, Mr Emmanuel Jime of the All Progressives Congress (APC), who polled 345,155 votes. The INEC Returning Officer for the election, Prof. Sabastine Maimako, declared the result on Sunday in Makurdi. He said that Ortom “having polled the highest number of votes at this election is hereby declared winner”. Maimako said the total registered votes were 2,471,894, total accredited voters were 858,947 while total valid votes stood at 830,954.